<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="87" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[173,659,1682,1729]" box="[197,659,1682,1703]" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,301,1682,1703]" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species most closely resembles
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[173,659,1682,1729]" box="[173,659,1708,1729]" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">
<taxonomicName box="[173,256,1708,1729]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabae">
<emphasis box="[173,256,1708,1729]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">C. sabae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to its entirely red pronotum; however,
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[707,1194,194,1729]" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">
it can be distinguished by the humeral and first discal blue maculae confluent and the elytra with bluish green cast at apex (
<figureCitation box="[979,1043,247,268]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="1.[175,215,1570,1589]" captionTargetBox="[222,1165,184,1547]" captionTargetId="figure-57@1.[151,1171,183,1574]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Figs. 1–4. Chrysobothris species, dorsal habitus. 1) C. sabae; 2) C. hispaniolae; 3) C. thoracica; 4) C. marskeae." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4893208" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4893208/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Furthermore, the male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[888,945,274,295]" captionStart="Figs" captionStartId="3.[175,215,1710,1729]" captionTargetBox="[159,1166,1288,1687]" captionTargetId="figure-499@3.[151,1171,1288,1687]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Figs. 5–7. Chrysobothris species, male genitalia. 5) C. sabae; 6) C. marskeae; 7) C. thoracica." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4893212" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4893212/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
) differ from all other species of the group, with a broader apex of the median lobe than that seen in 
<taxonomicName box="[944,1034,327,348]" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sabae">
<emphasis box="[944,1034,327,348]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">C. sabae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Schaeffer" authorityYear="1905" class="Insecta" family="Buprestidae" genus="Chrysobothris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="87" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="thoracica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">Chrysobothris thoracica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from throughout the 
<collectingCountry name="Virgin Islands" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">Virgin Islands</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[832,955,380,401]" name="Puerto Rico" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">Puerto Rico</collectingCountry>
. For a full description, see Woodley and Touroult (2012).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[707,1194,194,1729]" box="[731,947,433,455]" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,810,433,454]" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">Length.</emphasis>
<quantity box="[824,943,433,455]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.6" metricValueMax="6.7" metricValueMin="4.5" pageId="6" pageNumber="87" unit="mm" value="5.6" valueMax="6.7" valueMin="4.5">4.5–6.7 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
