<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="87" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="6.[707,1194,194,1729]" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[731,812,1575,1596]" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">Biology.</emphasis>
This species has been swept from the shrub 
<taxonomicName box="[766,867,1602,1623]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[766,832,1602,1623]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">Croton</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
(
<taxonomicName box="[880,1024,1602,1623]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="6" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Euphorbiaceae</taxonomicName>
) and beaten from dead vines and the tree 
<taxonomicName box="[956,1081,1629,1650]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Combretaceae" genus="Laguncularia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="6" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="racemosa">
<emphasis box="[956,1081,1629,1650]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">L. racemosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, MAI has taken it repeatedly from living trees of 
<taxonomicName authority="Sw." authorityName="Sw." box="[707,941,1682,1703]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nyctaginaceae" genus="Pisonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="6" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="subcordata">
<emphasis box="[707,894,1682,1703]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="87">Pisonia subcordata</emphasis>
Sw.
</taxonomicName>
, (loblolly/water mampoo, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="de Jussieu" authorityYear="1789" box="[707,850,1708,1729]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Nyctaginaceae" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="6" pageNumber="87" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="family">Nyctaginaceae</taxonomicName>
), suggesting this may be a true host.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
